cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the theft of model weights of convolutional neural networks, which is a topic related to machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the complexity of the dataset and proposes a new metric, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper uses i.i.d. noise inputs to steal the weights, which is related to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
